We had some success using just the omni wheels for odometry, just need to be mindful of the very small amount of acceleration and deceleration you can do before the wheels start slipping. We used a vector that added up the contribution of each wheel and then rotated that robot relative vector based on the gyro angle to get the final X and Y position on the field.

//Absolute position

this.dPosition = new Vect((-left+right)/Math.sqrt(3), left/3.0 + right/3.0 - 2/3.0*back);

this.dPosition = dPosition.rotate(this.getAngle());

position = position.add(this.dPosition);
